Name: Outer World Kepa Raider

Description: It is unknown if Vubbe Fighters are trained to be like that or born that way. Sometimes, wrong definitions become so widespread that it is hard to change them later on. This is one of those cases.
Name: Outer World Vubbe Fighter

Description: It is said that Deadborn have a chance of becoming Rodelin if they are strongly influenced by demons or are recognized by high ranking demons. Among those, a few are known to be able to go back and forth between our world and the demonic world.
Name: Outer World Rodelin

Description: A monster that has become much larger than it's original form. It used to be about the size of an adult human's little finger. It is sometimes hard to differentiate those that have been affected by Medzio Diena.
Name: Outer World Cronewt

Description: Pantos used to live in Gele region for a long time and before it was influnced on Medzio Diena, it kept its close relationship with humans. Even if the Panto is totally different from normal Pantos, they originated from our world.
Name: Outer World Large Panto Spearman

Description: When the demons found Glizardons, they immediately subjugated them into minions. Glizardons that aren't minions are still dangerous to humans.
Name: Outer World Glizardon

Description: A somewhat cute mutant that is always expressionless. They assemble together when chanting.
Name: Outer World Moya

Description: Operor are monsters that are unusually close to their original form, but have had their aggressiveness and violent tendencies enhanced. It is a specimen that had been in a coma after coming back from the demonic world.
Name: Outer World White Operor

Description: It is a monster from the demon realm that the Demon King Vaiga uses. Vaiga likes monsters that reports news from various worlds.
Name: Outer World Loftlem

Description: Though it is a legend that cannot be confirmed, Harpeia used to follow Goddess Laima instead of the demons. People point to Harpeia of this color to support their theories.
Name: Outer World White Harpeia

Description: As a monster of mineral-type mutation, it is unclear why it bears resemblance to a whale.
Name: Outer World Stone Whale

Description: Ghost caused by demon might increase the rank by receiving more stronger power if endures more than 100 years.
Name: Outer World Specter Monarch

Description: Even the demons who caused Medzio Diena didn't know the Magburks around them would turn out like this.
Name: Outer World Magburk

Description: This monster who betrayed Goddess Gabija can be called the heretic of the spirits.
Name: Outer World Fire Lord

Description: Nederbovine bases its origin on the demon realm. This is not an intelligent demon. It is a beast that is being raised by demons.
Name: Outer World Netherbovine

Description: The demons are trying to give the Manticen great power so they can control other insect-type monsters.
Name: Outer World Manticen

Description: The most difficult aspect about dealing with these monsters is that they can appear in people's houses unexpectedly.
Name: Outer World Mushwort

Name: Red Lavenzard

Description: Akhlass type monsters are demons, but originate from our world. The Akhlass Dame is one that has re-transformed after gaining human essence.
Name: Akhlass Dame

Description: The armor of Akhlass Tikke shows what the Tikke wishes to become. The estrangement is somewhat saddening.
Name: Akhlass Tikke

Description: The Akhlass absorb human essence when they become demons. By doing so, they acquire desires that they don't have as bats. The difference is much more stronger among Beorns than Tikke.
Name: Akhlass Beorn

Description: Akhlass Sensors enjoy absorbing and emitting the energy of demons. They become stronger through this process.
Name: Akhlass Sensor

Description: Unlike other Akhlass, the Humps do not have any aspirations related to humans. They believe that humans must cease to exist as there is nothing else to be learned from them.
Name: Akhlass Hump

Description: The Akhlass Petals wish to become a Countess by proving their worth. As such, they also like to order those around as much as they like to fight themselves.
Name: Akhlass Petal

Description: Akhlass Steel have a tendancy to fight as they wish instead of following the orders of others.
Name: Akhlass Steel

Description: The Akhlacia are not as high up the hierarchy as they initially seem. They are more like maids for nobles. In other words, their class is in accordance to their owner.
Name: Akhlacia

Description: All Akhlass Bishops are ambitious and will scheme about climbing the demon social ladder at any chance.

Description: There must only be one Akhlass Princess per region. If not, they will battle until there is only one left standing. If there are more than one per region, this is a sure sign of there being an even higher ranking demon controlling them.

Description: The lifespan of a Castle Princess is rarely more than one hundred years. This is unusually short for a demon. As such, they try every method of extending this short lifespan including magic, vampirism, alchemy and much more.
Name: Castle Princess

Description: It's nickname is the one who was swallowed first. According to rumors, it has gained it's current appearance after being swallowed by Gesti and being reincarnated. It is unknown if Diena is actually loyal to Gesti despite following her orders. If Giltine did actually warn Gesti against giving power to Diena, then it might mean that Diena still has a hatred of them. Her name comes from when she was swallowed, during the day.
Name: Demon Lord Diena

Description: This monster is said to move without taking the rider's will into consideration.
Name: Escarot

Description: The Kugheri believe that the world changes based on three different reasons, and how it looks depends on which reason is the strongest. The Kugheri Balzermancer is the leading Kugheri of this faith and is more of a shaman than a priest.

Description: It is commonly thought to be a monster derived from a hedgehog, but nobody is quite certain. There are quite a few scholars that suggest it is derived from vegetation.
Name: Gosaru

Description: There are rumors saying the Weaver is looking for thread made of stone.
Name: Weaver

Description: Their numbers grew after the Great Plant Cataclysm; now they tend to compete with humans for territory.
Name: Chupacabra

Description: Velcoffer Guards aren't demons, but regular animals that mutated into monsters. What's more, the advent of these beasts wasn't caused by Medzio Diena. The Sage Master speculates that they were one of the monster species said to have been exiled from our world in a joint effort by goddesses and demons. As there are no records of these monsters prior to Medzio Diena, it's possible that the disaster set them free from the seals that detained them.
Name: Velcoffer

Description: It is not uncommon for inanimate objects to become monsters after Medzio Diena, but the appearance of candlesticks on the heads of existing monsters remains a curious phenomenon.
Name: Candle Logger

Description: According to a courageous observer, the two heads often quarrel with each other. If it weren't for their anatomy preventing either head from hurting the other, murder-suicides would likely be a common occurrence.
Name: Porahound

Description: A monster born on Medzio Diena. After discovering these monsters, the demons trained them to pull carriages, and sent those with good combat abilities to the human realm.
Name: Vel's Chariot

Description: Velnippers are the strongest of all Insect type monsters. They aren't invincible, but their chances of defeating other Insect monsters are high due to the venom they produce, which is particularly lethal to insects.
Name: Velnipper

Description: This insect predator evolved to grow into a larger body, meaning it must now hunt and consume prey in large quantities to survive. That is, in fact, the reason why this species is not as abundant as others.
Name: Jezebel

Description: For centuries Demon Lord Solcomm has attempted to attack the Astral Tower and Pbeta traveled between the demon realm and our world to aid him. But deep down, Pbeta was dissatisfied and his resentment against Solcomm grew. One day, Pbeta was unable to bear with Solcomm any longer and decided to revolt against him.

Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons.

Name: Blue Nuo

Description: Warpulis is one that gets along nicely with Demon Lord Kartas as they both have fickle personalities. It seems as if Chaos itself has worked itself into this being as Warpulis is ready to sneer at it's opponents while brutally attacking them. As such, no other Demon Lord is interested in keeping Warpulis as a minion. Only Demon Lord Kartas seems to be able to handle Warpulis.
Name: Demon Lord Warpulis

Description: There are of course normal books in the Goddess' Fantasy Library. However, there are also many that are made of materials unknown to humans. Lapinels live in the 2nd dimension that is located between the bookshelves that contain such books. They spread to many worlds once they pop out of their books.
Name: Lapinel

Description: Succubus are following Demon Lord Naktis' orders, but it is said that they aren't happy with how things are going.
Name: Succubus

Description: Stone Frosters are monsters derived from steel, limestone and moss that were on the seashore. We have yet to see the many variations of this monster.
Name: Stonefroster

Description: Oh you poor wanderer whom has many burdens of sin balanced on your back.. part of a poem given to Gorkas by the previous Sage Master.
Name: Gorkas

Description: Lavenzard are monsters from the demonic world that volunteered to come to our world in order to avoid being trapped as punishment.
Name: Lavenzard

Description: We can tell Lape society is gradually becoming more complex and differentiated by looking at them distinguishing themselves from each other for even slight differences between them. When humans see them, they look the same, but they differentiate themselves from each other by having different names so humans also call them differently.
Name: Rafene

Description: The monster used to be a small and insignificant creature that lurked on swamp bottoms before Medzio Diena. Little is known of it's transformation.
Name: Armaos

Description: The Froster Lord is a reagent for a world destroyed by Giltine that has frozen over.
Name: Froster Lord

Description: Each Woodspirit has various personalities. Unlike the outline color, there are various it such as solo play and demon's pawn. But, there are no Woodspirit which have a like to a human.
Name: Woodspirit

Description: Although Teal Specter is dead, Medzio Diena has allowed his spirit to remain. Due to the strong magic he possessed in life, his spirit has a different composition from that of other specters.
Name: Teal Specter

Description: A possessed demonic monster obsessed with the divine Goddess Statues.
Name: Shardstatue

Description: An unnamed Master is known to have said that if there was a bit of intervention from the Goddess', some monsters may have fought for the humans. The main example of such a monster is the Taumas. Unlike the Goddess', the demons were successful in bringing many monsters to their side.
Name: Terra Taumas

Description: Gremlin are monsters that live in the demonic world or other strange spaces. They came to our world during Medzio Diena and usually lost their flying abilities.
Name: Terra Gremlin

Description: It is known that the tail is used when they compete against each other, but you should not just rely on such tendency.
Name: Terra Mallet Wyvern

Description: It is little ambiguous which types of lives become the source of Gaigalas. It is suspicious if they existed in our world.
Name: Terra Gaigalas

Description: Old Status that Goddess' divinity left from here will absorb the demons.
Name: Ominous Stone Statue

Description: Many people are participating on the efforts to prevent them from producing offspring by spurting out spores.
Name: Terra Rytaswort

Description: The Akhlass Petals wish to become a Countess by proving their worth. As such, they also like to order those around as much as they like to fight themselves.
Name: Akhlass Petal

Description: Akhlass Steel have a tendancy to fight as they wish instead of following the orders of others.
Name: Akhlass Steel

Description: The Akhlacia are not as high up the hierarchy as they initially seem. They are more like maids for nobles. In other words, their class is in accordance to their owner.
Name: Akhlacia

Description: All Akhlass Bishops are ambitious and will scheme about climbing the demon social ladder at any chance.
Name: Akhlass Bishop

Description: The Countess has extremely good hearing even among the Akhlass. It is said that they are able to hear conversations that others can't hear.
Name: Akhlass Countess

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Tots will never betray anyone that they have a connection to. The issue is that they don't seem to make connections with humans.
Name: Kugheri Tot

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. Sommi usually like to be revered by others and will help those that revere them.
Name: Kugheri Sommi

Description: Other Kugheri will often ride or use it to transport luggage.
Name: Kugheri Lyoni

Description: The connection of Numani is incomparable to others. They only respect those that are spiritually stronger than themselves.
Name: Kugheri Numani

Description: The mental state of Kugheri Zeuni has not been properly recorded anywhere.
Name: Kugheri Zeuni

Description: Kugheri have strong mental connections. The only way to resolve a feud with a Balzer is to kill it or be killed.
Name: Kugheri Balzer

Description: The Rodejokel is a foot soldier of the Rode society.
Name: Rodejokel

Description: The Rhodenabean are the common folk in the Rhode society and will use whatever is in their hands as weapons.
Name: Rhodenabean

Description: Rhodenags are usually workers. They use their tools to pick fruit or work the soil.
Name: Rhodenag

Description: Monster born of the combination of magic stones and lake plants. Before Medzio Diena, they were spotted once every ten years on average. Now, they have increased in number and their population has become more difficult to control.
Name: Lotuscat

Description: Pates are known to appear in lakes when the quality of the water is low. These monsters existed prior to Medzio Diena.
Name: Pate

Description: Coteries live in groups across all kinds of aquatic habitats, from ocean trenches to continental freshwater bodies.
Name: Coterie

Description: Lilly Maids existed prior to Medzio Diena. Before the Schaffenstar began producing chemical baits for them, they were known to lure and drown local lake dwellers.
Name: Lilly Maid

Description: These monsters were once curbstones in the demon world that came to life when Demon Lord Solcomm enchanted them to become part of his troops.
Name: Spinacho

Description: Rubetas are an extremely prolific species. Despite being the most commonly hunted monster in the heydays of the Schaffenstar, they continue to prosper after Medzio Diena.
Name: Rubeta

Description: Little Rubetas can be frequently spotted after Medzio Diena. They did exist prior to that, but Rubetas develop quickly enough that it was rare to come across an infant. Nowadays, their growing numbers have made young Rubetas more common than ever.
Name: Little Rubeta

Description: Long ago, it was thought that Noli Maids buried the lower half of their bodies under rocks to camouflage as flowers. Now we know that their roots gain mobility as the Maids turns into adults.
Name: Noli Maid

Description: Curiously, some Kindron have been known to live in fresh water after Medzio Diena. They are found not only in estuaries but far from the sea in continental lakes as well.
Name: Beissen

Description: Before Ignas took control of the Astral Tower, the water of the Starlit Lake was lethal to demons. To solve this, Demon Lord Solcomm created the Mutts and commanded them to construct a passageway through the lake.
Name: Mutt

Description: Nastes are the materialization of Astral Tower Schaffenstar members transformed under the influence of the demons. Ignas controls their minds, forcing them to obey him.
Name: Naste

Description: Like Mad Lenses, Gleam Lens monsters were once magic lenses left behind by Lydia Schaffen that transformed under the effects of Medzio Diena.
Name: Gleam Lens

Description: Rabblers and Punters are closely related creatures that serve in the demon world as both livestock and hunting companions.
Name: Rabbler

Description: Rumors tell that Wryers were once used as companions by Schaffenstar hunters before they became too ferocious and turned into monsters.
Name: Wryer

Description: Nasleias are former Schaffenstar members that were transformed by magic to serve Ignas. It is said that they have no recollection of their lives as humans.
Name: Nasleia

Description: Like Gleam Lenses, Mad Lens monsters were once magic lenses left behind by Lydia Schaffen that transformed under the effects of Medzio Diena.
Name: Mad Lens

Description: Grobs are thought to have been used by Ignas in his battles against the Resistance army, or by Solcomm in his attacks against the Schaffenstar. In either case, we know these monsters were introduced to the lake for combat purposes.
Name: Grob

Description: Some believe that Hafters may have once been the handles of telescopes placed around the Astral Tower. Conducting research at the Schaffenstar is impossible, however, so this hypothesis has never been confirmed.
Name: Hafter

Description: One could wonder where all these wooden barrels could have come from to transform into monsters, but the truth is that they are a common object found in any human assemblage.
Name: Waglog

Description: The Astral Tower is independently governed by the Schaffenstar, so research on the monsters that inhabit it is scarce. Because of this, we do not know whether Glove Golems appeared due to Medzio Diena or if Ignas created them voluntarily.
Name: Glove Golem

Description: These monsters were brought into the Astral Tower after Ignas joined sides with the demons. They are said to inhabit extreme locations in the demon realm.
Name: Punter

Description: These creatures turned into monsters and began walking upright after Medzio Diena. Unable to return to their underground habitats, they began to hunt on the surface.
Name: Moltooth

Description: Besides the fact that they originate from the demon realm, little is known about Bishopstars. Perhaps more will be revealed when future humans explore the demon world.
Name: Bishop Star

Description: These monsters were pieces of furniture from the Fallen City that came to life after Medzio Diena. Many are the wooden objects that became monsters after that tragic day.
Name: Wajak Walker

Description: Horong Walkers were born of a strange mutation involving will-o'-the-wisps.
Name: Horong Walker

Description: Bishop Grays are said to be the clerics of the demon world, serving the Demon Goddess Ragana.
Name: Bishop Gray

Description: Bishop Points are under the command of demon-world clerics who serve the Demon Goddess Ragana. Although she is only a minor figure in the demon realm, Ragana doesn't seem to cherish them as her followers.
Name: Bishop Point

Description: Kigles are monsters transformed from small-scale secret weapons of the Royal Army.
Name: Kigle

Description: Kigles are monsters transformed from secret weapons of the Royal Army, after their magic began to react to the events of Medzio Diena. After that, General Lhamin halted the production of the weapons, and nowadays they are longer found in the Royal Army.
Name: Kigle Lops

Description: Bishop Blancos are said to perform the role of altar servers to Demon Goddess Ragana. That is only an analogy, of course, as there is no direct equivalent in the human world.
Name: Bishop Blanco

Description: Bishop Harts are demon-world clerics under the command of demon religious orders who serve Demon Goddess Ragana.
Name: Bishop Hart

Description: Poncers are at the top of the food chain in their habitat. They can easily take down a human soldier and, despite their power, they are known to attack only in large groups, making them virtually invincible. Their small stature, however, means that they can become targets to other strong creatures when they are alone.
Name: Poncer

Description: Species in the Yishon family were once nocturnal animals that lived in groups, until Medzio Diena turned them into monsters.
Name: Yishoneer

Description: Species in the Yishon family were once nocturnal animals that lived in groups, until Medzio Diena turned them into monsters. Some became active during the daytime and lost their eyesight, but at the same time they learned to use simple tools.
Name: Yishon Torcher

Description: Cave Stonacorns originated from plant seeds mixed in the excrements of bats and other creatures.
Name: Cave Stonacorn

Description: Solcomm is a Demon Lord that was quite skilled but had the misfortune of meeting a bad leader, a skilled opponent such as Lydia Schaffen, fighting in unfavorable terrain, having bad minions and choosing the wrong allies. In other words, Solcomm was the unluckiest Demon Lord.
Name: Demon Lord Solcomm

Description: Kindron Leaders are called that because they tend to stand at the front in battles. Unlike their moniker, however, their position is rather low in the Kindron hierarchy.
Name: Kindron Leader

Description: All Kindron species that adapted to freshwater habitats eventually separated from Goddess Jurate. At sea, there are still Kindrons who follow the goddess, although they constitute a minority.
Name: Kindron Boor

Description: Most people believe Humming Dukes to be a gruesome hybrid species that combines mosquitoes and insects created after Medzio Diena.
Name: Humming Duke

Description: These monsters were responsible for leading the negotiations of the Night Panto agreement. We know for sure that Night Pantos entered the Astral Tower after the agreement, although it is still uncertain how they arrived in the Fallen City. The contents of that agreement also remain unknown.
Name: Night Panto Mage

Description: In his efforts to annihilate the Resistance, Ignas acquired the Pipis before Medzio Diena and hatched them to serve in his own army.
Name: Pipi

Description: Well-grown Piangs become Vesperas. According to rumors, they once helped Ignas gain the upper hand in a battle against the Resistance.
Name: Vespera

Description: These monsters settled in the Kingdom's capital after it became a site of ruins. Because of that, they suffered little influence from Medzio Diena and have maintained most of their original form.
Name: Beetlegreen

Description: Besides the larger body, Bumblegreens have remained mostly unchanged since Medzio Diena. That said, they have become incredibly adaptable to new environments.
Name: Bumblegreen

Description: It is said that Night Panto Archers are set to receive access to the archery secrets in the Astral Tower after the end of their contract. Alas, that which they covet the most will never be theirs.
Name: Night Panto Archer

Description: Ignas created the Nastudeu by cursing members of the Schaffenstar with his own blood and transforming them. Unlike Nastes and Nasleias, however, theoretically it should be impossible to return the Nastudeu to their original form.
Name: Nastudeu

Description: An unknown agreement of cooperation with the demons is known to have given special powers to a large number of Pantos, which have since changed into a new appearance. Although the other party in the agreement is not a demon, they are suspected to work in conjunction with them.
Name: Night Panto Stellar

Description: Pipis who hatch become Piangs. Their stages of development are said to apply differently in the demon realm.
Name: Piang

Description: Mushutas transformed from mushrooms grown in cold regions. In northern provinces of the Kingdom, local sayings warn against mushrooms grown under the aurora. Many believe these monsters appeared at the Starlit Lake due to its starlight-attracting properties.
Name: Mushuta

Description: Most small Insect types exist in large numbers. Trippies are an exception, as their populations are smaller than those of similarly-sized species.
Name: Trippy

Description: Bloks just appeared within the last year, so there isn't much information about it yet.
Name: Blok Archer

Description: Bloks just appeared within the last year, so there isn't much information about it yet.
Name: Blok Magician

Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Name: Lichenclops

Description: The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Name: Lichenclops Mage

Description: There are quite a few reckless people who are going after the monsters that have big ores like the Kenol attached onto the bodies of the monsters. It would have been better if they had acted more cautiously when thinking about the disaster that was brought to the world.
Name: Kenol

Description: The edges of its wings are covered in poison. Touching it may cause paralysis.
Name: Leafly

Description: Neop was recently promoted as a Demon Lord by Giltine in order to disturb Laima's plans. Because of the promotion, he tries hard to learn more.
Name: Neop

Description: A magical levitation stone from the Starlit Lake that turned into a monster during Medzio Diena. It was thought to only exist near Starlit Lake since most of the magical levitation stones throughout human history were used there, but it seems as if the Kedoran Merchant Alliance and Agailla Flurry had quite a few of their own.
Name: Lake Golem

Description: Fondus were known to occasionally appear near Starlit Lake even before Medzio Diena. There was a massive increase in their population after Medzio Diena. The liquid on top of the Fondus is an extremely rare foodstuff. It costs a fortune to detoxicate it enough to be fit for human consumption. It may be put back on the tables of nobles if the Schaffen Star manages to recover.
Name: Fondus

Description: If you are pressed into finding a human society equivalent, the closest thing would be an independent mercenary. Of course, this doesn't mean that the Gunner has no loyalties. Varle social tendencies are difficult for a normal person to understand.
Name: Varle Gunner

Description: The Varle will fight other Varle if not from the same group. The Varle Hench is usually in charge of pioneering and scouting and is normally the first to fall.
Name: Varle Hench

Description: After Medzio Diena, oceanic creatures chose one of three paths whether they had mutated or not. They could still follow Goddess Jurate, cooperate with the demons, or act independently. While the Varle are independent, they had always had a certain dislike for humans making many think that they are cooperating with demons. Varle Skippers are among the leading elite of the Varle society.
Name: Varle Skipper

Description: Despite what they may look and act like, Varle Henchmen are even more important than Varle Skippers. That is because the influence of Varle Skippers are measured in how many Varle Henchmen are following them. As such, a Varle Skipper without any Varle Henchmen is nothing more than an empty flag.
Name: Varle Henchmen

Description: Varle Anchors are usually older Varle, which might seem surprising. Of course, there are younger Varle as well, but this is because they are well experienced. While Anchors will also participate in battle, they are used to show their dominance over a certain area.
Name: Varle Anchor

Description: According to Varle societal rules, the Skipper has seniority over the Helmsman. However, the Helmsman can beat the Skipper to a pulp if the Henchmen support him and choose to lead the group in a different direction. This doesn't mean that the defeated Skipper is exiled. Only Goddess Jurate might understand this madness.
Name: Varle Helmsman

Description: The Anchor Golem is a monster that is derived from the linkage in the magical levitation stone.
Name: Anchor Golem

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Mages are usually affected more by divine energy.
Name: Tala Wizard

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Archers have been affected more by demons, at least in theory.
Name: Tala Archer

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about.
Name: Tala Battle Boss

Description: Lakhorn are monsters that appeared from the underworld where humans are not able to go to and have managed to emerge above ground.
Name: Lakhorn

Description: Lakhtanon are said to have been born in underground lakes or rivers. However, there are traces of civilization on them. There are people that say that this is because humans used to live underground a long time ago.
Name: Lakhtanon

Description: Lakhof are minerals from underground rivers that transformed on Medzio Diena. They have managed to come above ground since then.
Name: Lakhof

Description: It is more accurate to say that the Bavon levitates rather than flies. Bavon of this color have plant-like characteristics which means that it can go a long while without eating.
Name: Green Bavon

Description: The fragments or the broken pieces of Golem are reborn with new forms. Rublem is one of those.
Name: Green Rubblem

Description: The difference between a Zolem and a Golem is the movement with a spirit and not by magic.
Name: Green Zolem

Description: In the past, Nicopolis wizards grew these magic creatures by winding the springs on their backs to generate vines, which they used for gardening. After the accident of Nicopolis, however, they were affected by Medzio Diena and became the monsters they are today.
Name: Vine Walker

Description: A few monster experiments created by the wizards of old Nicopolis have begun to reappear after Medzio Diena. Considering how commonly Moyas are used in experiments, Crescent Moyas are likely one of the species' many varieties.
Name: Crescent Moya

Description: Before their mysterious disappearance, the wizards of Nicopolis were known to conduct various experiments on monsters. One of those monsters was the species we now call Wiza Moya.
Name: Wiza Moya

Description: Most of these monsters are old residents of Nicopolis who turned into slime. After a tragic experiment caused them all to disappear, Medzio Diena caused many to return to our world in the form of slime.
Name: Slime Witch

Description: Curiously, some Kindron have been known to live in fresh water after Medzio Diena. They are found not only in estuaries but far from the sea in continental lakes as well.
Name: Kindron Shooter

Description: Since Medzio Diena, amphibians have became to various forms, so Tutu seems as same as the original form. Of course, it is ferocious.
Name: Tutu

Description: Vesperias are the last stage of development of their species. These monsters could have caused serious damage to the Resistance army, if it weren't for the Masters' timely support.
Name: Vesperia

Description: For generations, the wizards of Nicopolis experimented with all sorts of magic creatures. Mimorats were the products of their first experiments on common rats.
Name: Mimorat Purple

Description: Mimorat Whites were created to carry goods on their backs. Even after the wizards of Nicopolis disappeared, these Mimorats survived and have since developed tastes of their own.
Name: Mimorat White

Description: Mimorat Pinks have evolved from Mimorat Whites according to the tastes of the species. Pinks like to collect and carry all sorts of objects, with some objects becoming more popular than others in light of the latest trends.
Name: Mimorat Pink

Description: Greens suffered the most radical transformations out of all the Mimorats after Medzio Diena. There is no telling why some were more affected than others, especially considering that all Mimorats belong to the same species.
Name: Mimorat Green

Description: These creatures were created as prisons according to the tastes of Nicopolis wizards. They became abandoned after the great accident, then turned into the monsters they are today with the influence of Medzio Diena.
Name: Haunted House

Description: These Nicopolis wizards who disappeared after the great accident and returned to our world as slime also lost their arms in the process, so they created a pair of slime arms that move by telekinesis. After that, they continued to conduct experiments and managed to cause another major accident.
Name: Slime Wizard

Description: These creatures originate from a failed experiment of a Nicopolis wizard who attempted to produce easy-to-read magic books. A cute mistake in the history of the city.
Name: Popup Cat

Description: Slime Gemini are the product of a failed experiment by Nicopolis wizards who returned to our world as slime and attempted to regain their human form by cloning themselves. Most residents of Nicopolis who were lost in the great accident and reappeared after Medzio Diena aren't very pleasant to look at.
Name: Slime Gemini

Description: The Varle King is the most revered among all Varle. Many Varle King are cooperating with Demon Lord Kartas in order to widen their realms. Those from the Zealot Order dislike all that have betrayed Goddess Jurate and they especially dislike the Varle Kings.
Name: Varle King

Description: She was one of the three wizards who ruled Nicopolis. After eliminating the capital and the court with a magic that affects only living beings, her ambitious experiments failed and caused the disappearance of all the residents of Nicopolis. She remained dormant in the form of dead matter, until the events of Medzio Diena brought her back to life.
Link_Drops: [{"Item": {"$ID": -1, "Name": "Silver", "Icon": "icon_item_silver2"}, "Chance": 0.0, "Quantity_MAX": 1, "Quantity_MIN": 1}]
Name: Pervading Queen

Description: Velcoffer Guards aren't demons, but regular animals that mutated into monsters. What's more, the advent of these beasts wasn't caused by Medzio Diena. The Sage Master speculates that they were one of the monster species said to have been exiled from our world in a joint effort by goddesses and demons. As there are no records of these monsters prior to Medzio Diena, it's possible that the disaster set them free from the seals that detained them.
Name: Velcoffer

Description: Nederbovine bases it's origin to the demon realm. This is not an intelligent demon. It is a beast that is being raised by the demons.
Name: Tera Netherbovine

Description: He has the tendency to control evil spirits and steal the power from those who do not obey him in order to accumulate even greater power.
Name: Tera Necroventer

Description: Ghost caused by demons has various form's features and color.
Name: Tera Specter Monarch

Description: Glackuman who dreams to become a famous fighter is only satisfied if he is dispatched to locations where a lot of fights are taking place.
Name: Tera Glackuman

Description: The transformation of the Canceril is now even considered ordinary in the world full of monsters derived from all sorts of lifeforms.
Name: Tera Canceril

Description: A long time ago, there were times that they were tamed and mounted by humans.
Name: Tera Silva Griffin

Description: You shouldn't just think of it as a beast of the demons. This monster is actually intelligent!
Name: Tera Velnia Monkey

Description: Violence and cruelty is normal in this place so it's a perfect place for demons. They enjoyed tortures and killings in the demon realm.
Name: Tera Prison Cutter

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Tera Red Lavenzard

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Tera Foculus

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Tera Rocksodon

Description: The most dramatic change the Goblin society experienced on Medzio Diena is the appearances of the strong individuals like the Templeshooter. However, they prioritize their individual benefits more than the Goblin tribe. Even if they serve for others, there's a certain possibility that they have hidden purposes.
Name: Templeshooter

Description: The seeds that dropped from leaf molds combined with larvas and turned into monsters. Of course, they weren't discovered before Medzio Diena.
Name: Moyabruka

Description: It is fortunate that there aren't many cases that the host became a monster, but it's a difficult phenomenon to understand.
Name: Mothstem

Description: When a low-ranked monster becomes strong, there are people who still think they are weak. If you don't pay attention to all changes in the current circumstances, these kinds of monsters may become disasters anytime.
Name: Flammidus

Description: The souls of those who ventured to the underworld now appear as demons.
Name: Evil Spirit

Description: According to legend this watchdog is a creation that Zachariel the Great had planned to preserve.
Name: Venucelos

Description: They kill their fellow demons out of boredom.
Name: Prison Fighter

Description: It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the demon realm and has gone through a lot of change.
Name: Red Old Hook

Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons.
Name: Nuo

Description: Pag members belong to the high class among other demons. The other demon also feels fear due to their cruelty. Pags only bully other demons who are not strong under the Demon King Kartas' guard, they appeared with the request by Giltine in this world.
Name: Pag Nat

Name: Dimension Minos

Name: Dimension Armori

Description: It is not known whether these monsters transformed after Medzio Diena and moved from the sea to the land as a result or if they are originally demonic beings. Goddess Jurate is not interested in them.

Description: We don't know which monster's mini version Infroburks are. One thing for sure is that they are vicious.
Name: Dimension Infroburk

Description: They kill their fellow demons out of boredom.

Description: Some that live inland don't believe that a crab of this size could have existed, but the Greentoshell was actually this size even before Medzio Diena. However, it's growth rate has been greatly accelerated and is now able to grow and live almost indefinitely. As such, there are many more Greentoshell that actually grow to be this size.
Name: Dimension Greentoshell

Description: A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.
Name: Dimension Infrorocktor

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complicated.
Name: Dimension High Vubbe

Description: Because of its appearance, novice miners often try to mine the crystal on the spider's back and are attacked.
Name: Dimension Crystal Spider

Name: Dimension Bat

Description: Hogma is smarter than the Vubbes so they use tools, but due to its strong instinct, it tends to make mistakes and hardly makes any progress.
Name: Dimension Hogma Warrior

Description: Levelheaded Hogmas are often seen taking the role of archers.
Name: Dimension Hogma Archer

Description: Among the Hogmas, there is someone who obtained the abilities through experiences. But, a sorcerer is not free from the instinct of a Hogma.
Name: Dimension Hogma Shaman

Description: It is said that they receive their powers from human souls because they gather toward the injured.
Name: Dimension Ellom

Description: Merog variant. Slight differences in the mutation process differentiates the variety of Merogs.
Name: Dimension Merog Shaman

Description: This reptile monster attacks instinctively but shows as much abilities as its intelligence.
Name: Dimension Merog Stinger

Description: Unlike popular belief, their role is to make sure that other Hogma???ontinue to fight, not to coordinate attacks.
Name: Dimension Hogma Captain

Description: A monster which is said to be created by demons using the Chupacabra.
Name: Dimension Chupaluka

Description: It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.
Name: Dimension Ellomago

Description: It is fierce against other monsters and humans, more so especially with Insect-type monsters.

Description: Amphibians that have branched out and evolved to be able to hunt in arid areas, travelers should be wary of them.
Name: Dimension Groll

Description: A monster with a habit of baiting and attacking humans.

Description: It is a beast type monster as can be seen in it's appearance and name. Of course, it originates in the demonic world, not ours.
Name: Dimension Lizardman

Description: Tama is a monster originating from the spores of some plants. It is unclear whether it will still grow from its current form.
Name: Dimension Tama

Description: It has no relation with the Kepa. They are demonic beasts even if they do have a rather high intelligence.
Name: Dimension Kepari

Description: One of the largest changes after the disappearance of the Goddess' is the fact that underwater creatures started to live on land. Their respiratory organs and blood composition have changed as they started to live on land which caused there to be many colors of Kodomor. Their diet has also changed to accommodate for the change in living conditions.
Name: Dimension Kodomor

Description: It still tends to gravitate toward rotten flesh.
Name: Dimension Kowak

Description: It hasn't been discovered yet from which inanimate being this monster tranformed from.
Name: Dimension Lemur

Description: Extremely resistant to the cold just like a Lemur. It may develop a yellowish color due to demonic energies.
Name: Dimension Lemuria

Description: While they look like guardsmen, these Hogmas have extensive battle experience.
Name: Dimension Hogma Soldier

Description: Compared to an average Hogma, they are much stronger, but their intelligence is lower.
Name: Dimension Hogma Scout

Description: It is a monster that is formed by binding an aninal with minenal. In recent years, various forms of these monsters have been discovered.
Name: Dimension Zinute

Description: It is a monster that is formed by binding an aninal with minenal. In recent years, various forms of these monsters have been discovered.
Name: Dimension Lauzinute

Description: Many types of Chupacabra have appeared all over the Kingdom, resulting in massive injuries and destruction of property. The Desert Chupacabra is one of the worst.
Name: Dimension Desert Chupacabra

Description: Although small, it has grown bigger than its original state and hunts for meat throughout its life
Name: Dimension Varv

Description: While it has no eyes, Arma has a highly developed sense of hearing and smell.
Name: Dimension Arma

Description: It attacks people with the bead that it is holding every day.
Name: Dimension Dimmer

Description: A monster variant that comes from a wizard's belongings. It is resistive to its original use.
Name: Dimension Flask

Description: A sad monster that can't fly.
Name: Dimension Phyracon

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Shaman Doll

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Black Shaman Doll

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Wizard Shaman Doll

Description: The Slime is an organism in the demon realm. Its population exploded after the time when the plant cataclysm, especially around the Mage Tower.
Name: Dimension Experimental Slime

Description: For the last several years, the Vubbe society became severely differentiated and complex. The number of Vubbe that are able to learn magic after Medzio Diena has greatly increased and their techniques are similar to that of earlier human wizards.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Wizard

Description: Vubbe Shaman only have meager powers and usually inspire other Vubbe through tattoos or drawings.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Shaman

Description: A monster whose habitat has been relocated close to the volcano.
Name: Dimension Chromadog

Description: It is a monster that has the power of various animals, so it is hard to face against.
Name: Dimension Rambear

Description: Ultanuns have always been flightless birds even before their deformation.
Name: Dimension Ultanun

Description: Don't let its cute appearance fool you. This monster will try to tear you apart, given the chance.
Name: Dimension Rubabos

Description: A somewhat cute mutant that is always expressionless. They assemble together when chanting.
Name: Dimension Moya

Description: Moyabu has evolved from the Moya. It is more violent than the Moya.
Name: Dimension Moyabu

Description: When it comes to flight, Bavon would be better just floating there as is.
Name: Dimension Bavon

Description: A carnivorous plant that uses bait to catch food. It shred its food into pieces before swallowing.
Name: Dimension Tanu

Description: A three headed monster. It is hard to tell whether the main body is just one head or all three.
Name: Dimension Zignuts

Description: The demons have tamed Denden and use it for their means.
Name: Dimension Denden

Description: If a moving poisonous mushroom makes you anxious, consider Doyor as an example.

Description: The yellow grass on its body looks supple. But if you touch it, it can be quite painful .
Name: Dimension Tipio

Description: The Rondo is not an animal found in our world, rather it is an animal that crossed from the demon realm.
Name: Dimension Rondo

Description: Although it appears to have no sharp edges, it will when engaged in battle.
Name: Dimension Caro

Description: There are not too many cases of a fruit deformed monsters. Leafnut belongs to these few cases.

Description: The flowers around its neck are actually real flowers rather than decorations.

Description: You will face its relentless anger if you carelessly touch it.
Name: Dimension Mali

Description: Be aware of the smoke that this creature spurts as it is highly toxic and will last for a while.

Description: A bite from its sharp beak causes persistent pain, which may last for a while.

Description: The edges of its wings are covered in poison. Touching it may cause paralysis.
Name: Dimension Leafly

Description: Although originally created to defend the Royal Mausoleum, it has since shifted into a state that attacks anyone who enters.

Description: Regardless of their color, Hohen Ritter play a central role in Hohen society. Hohen Mane and Hohen Mages sometimes lead Hohen Ritter but they still have pride in the fact that they are the main powers in their society.

Description: A specimen that has passed a sort of rite of passing in the Hohen society.

Description: A specimen that has passed a sort of rite of passing in the Hohen society.
Name: Dimension Green Hohen Barkle

Description: Hohen Mages are rather new in Hohen society. Demons that had lived in our world rather than the demonic world. Those that had great magical talents grew in number after Medzio Diena and became Hohen Mages. Their color is due to the side effects of dimensional travel.
Name: Dimension Blue Hohen Mage

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantageous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future. Red Hohen are loyal Hohen who are at the stage of being recognized as demons.
Name: Dimension Red Hohen Mage

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantageous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future. Red Hohen are loyal Hohen who are at the stage of being recognized as demons.
Name: Dimension Red Hohen Orben

Description: Hohen Orben play the role of prophet in their society but aren't treated particularly well, similar to how humans treat fortune tellers.
Name: Dimension Green Hohen Orben

Description: Hohen competed against humans since the birth of the kingdom. They were cooperative to demons instead of the goddesses, but they posed no big problems since their amount was small compared to humans. However, the environment that Medzio Diena changed is working more advantageous for Hohens instead of humans so it is not certain whether humans would have an edge over them in the future. Hohen of this color are known for enjoying bloodshed.

Description: Demons that follow Demon Lord Hauberk. They are still loyal to their lord even after he was ripped apart by Demon Lord Helgasercle. Harugal of this color enjoy hunting others. Of course, it is not because they require the food.
Name: Dimension Blue Harugal

Description: Demons that follow Demon Lord Hauberk. They are still loyal to their lord even after he was ripped apart by Demon Lord Helgasercle. Those that spent too much time under the demonic world's sun are this color.
Name: Dimension Brown Harugal

Description: A long time ago, Elet used to be a fairy or a soul. They received the curse of Goddess Ausrine and they hid into the human world and lived on. Since Medzio Diena, when the demons invaded the world, they are showing their determination to participate with the other demons. Those that successfully assassinated other demons decorate themselves with these colors.
Name: Dimension Blue Elet

Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons. Blue Nuo are similar to Kartas in that they enjoy bloodshed.
Name: Dimension Blue Nuo

Description: What's unique about Nuo is that they are subordinates of the Demon King Kartas. Although Kartas possesses a brutal and unexpected personality, it is so incredible that Nuo who is under the control of Kartas possesses the power and the number for the ones who know well about the circumstances in the demons. Those that are descendants of the Nuo that survived the volcanic eruption one thousand years ago are of this color.
Name: Dimension Red Nuo

Description: Nuka are under the control of the Demon King Baiga and were dispatched here to fulfill the tasks that Gesti received from Giltine. But, Gesti is controlling them unlike what Baiga once thought. Those that were punished by Gesti are of this color.

Description: Nuka are under the control of the Demon King Baiga and were dispatched here to fulfill the tasks that Gesti received from Giltine. But, Gesti is controlling them unlike what Baiga once thought. Those of this color are sensitive to the demonic world's sun.
Name: Dimension Brown Nuka

Description: Elma are one of Gesti's bodyguards that are used in various roles including the defense of the demonic world. Those of this color are said to have suffered side effects while coming to our world.
Name: Dimension Blue Elma

Description: Elma are one of Gesti's bodyguards that are used in various roles including the defense of the demonic world. Those of this color are due to the ficklet nature of Gesti.
Name: Dimension Red Elma

Description: It gets created when the stone pieces or the stone figures of the buildings which the demons stayed change.
Name: Dimension Blue Guardian Spider

Description: It gets created when the stone pieces or the stone figures of the buildings which the demons stayed change.
Name: Dimension Red Guardian Spider

Description: The Dumaro is not a newly discovered monster, but has developed new toxic abilities after the Great Plant Cataclysm. Dumaro of this color are skilled hunters.

Description: The Dumaro is not a newly discovered monster, but has developed new toxic abilities after the Great Plant Cataclysm. They are said to have a relation with the Brimstonia region of the demonic world.
Name: Dimension Yellow Dumaro

Description: The fact that the Wendigo is this color means that it has successfully hunted a large number of prey.
Name: Dimension Blue Wendigo

Description: This isn't a strong monster, but tears could be dropping from your eyes if you attack it recklessly.
Name: Dimension Kepa

Description: Despite its appearance, these creatures are not hollow on the inside.
Name: Dimension Leaf Bug

Description: Leaves fallen from a dead Hanaming wither rapidly.

Description: Originally stalks of plants, the Chinency have since evolved to their current form.
Name: Dimension Chinency

Description: A Popolion's voice is said to break even glass bottles.
Name: Dimension Popolion

Description: Despite its appearance, the Pokubu can be quite ferocious.

Description: Very little is known about the Jukopus' internal structure.
Name: Dimension Jukopus

Description: Adventurers should take special care of their belongings since they have a tendency of pulling pranks. Those that have stayed under the demonic world's sun for too long become this color.

Description: We can tell Lape society is gradually becoming more complex and differentiated by looking at them distinguishing themselves from each other for even slight differences between them. Name: Dimension Lapa Archer

Description: It is commonly thought to be a monster derived from a hedgehog, but nobody is quite certain. There are quite a few scholars that suggest it is derived from vegetation.

Description: We are not sure about the uses of the thorns that are on the back. There are many cases where transformed monsters keep their appearances before transformations even if they don't have any functions, but sometimes their functions get discovered later so scholars are not making any decisions yet.

Description: Polibu eats small animals or insects and they even eats dead bodies. But, they attack humans to have just one bite so you should be cautious.

Description: There are many cases that some parts of the plants become monsters. For Ponpons, the fruits had transformed.
Name: Dimension Ponpon

Description: It goes without saying that it would hurt a lot to get attacked by this monster's thick beak.
Name: Dimension Canchobird

Description: A monster that hates humans for unknown reasons. It will pick attacking humans over surviving or feeding. Red Truffle will tend not to eat fungi from their own bodies.

Description: It is simple and effective for Beeteros to camouflage. Please do not touch the swaying leaf as it can stab you.

Description: It is simple and effective for Beeteros to camouflage. Please do not touch the swaying leaf as it can stab you.

Name: Dimension Yekubite

Description: Although small, it has grown bigger than its original state and hunts for meat throughout its life
Name: Dimension Varv

Description: Acting as Mirtis' scout minion, these bats once lived throughout the world but have grown into a large threat despite their small bodies.
Name: Dimension Bat

Description: The souls of people that have set foot in the demonic world have started to appear for various reasons. Souls that have done much to earn respect in the demonic world are of this color.
Name: Dimension Black Banshee

Description: Vubbe Shaman only have meager powers and usually inspire other Vubbe through tattoos or drawings.
Name: Dimension Vubbe Shaman

Description: Be aware of the smoke that this creature spurts as it is highly toxic and will last for a while.
Name: Dimension Grummer

Description: Loktanun have always been flightless birds even before their deformation.
Name: Dimension Loktanun

Description: A young Rajapearl. The reason it is black is because it came into contact with a ghost during it's growth.
Name: Dimension Black Rajapearl

Description: A bite from its sharp beak causes persistent pain, which may last for a while.
Name: Dimension Brown Hummingbird

Description: Although slimes are similar in appearance, they vary in species due to differences between the materials they originated from.
Name: Dimension Blue Slime

Description: Merog variant. Slight differences in the mutation process differentiates the variety of Merogs.
Name: Dimension Merog Shaman

Description: This reptile monster attacks instinctively but shows as much abilities as its intelligence.
Name: Dimension Merog Stinger

Description: Originally created with good intentions, the golem now lives possessed by evil energy.

Description: The Pag are high ranking demons. Even other demons are frightened by their cruelty. Pag Clampers usually transport their victims or finish them off.

Description: The Pag are high ranking demons. Even other demons are frightened by their cruelty. Description: Wendigos are known for attacking humans as prey. Wendigo Escapees are thought to be those that have broken away from the group in order to have the prey for themselves.
Name: Dimension Wendigo Escapee

Description: Deadborns turn into Rodelins when they receive a lot of influences from demons or when they are acknowledged by the high-ranked demons.
Name: Dimension Rodelin

Description: A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.
Name: Dimension Red Infrorocktor

Description: Pyran is created when the egg of a reptile that is in ashes transforms and hatches.
Name: Dimension Pyran

Description: An animal that had been turned into a lesser demon a long time ago, they come in countless types due to their populous numbers.
Name: Dimension Drake

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Shaman Doll

Description: It is a monster that was transformed from the plants that grew from stones which the humans threw away after refining them on Medzio Diena.
Name: Dimension Blindlem

Description: While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
Name: Dimension Black Shaman Doll

Description: A monster whose habitat has been relocated close to the volcano.
Name: Dimension Chromadog

Description: These were originally from our world but became scarce after migrating to the demonic world. Their numbers have been increasing lately. Those that have been affected by ghosts may turn black.
Name: Dimension Black Drake

Description: By looking at the spear Ticen is carrrying, the assumption that there may be other kinds of Ticens turned out to be true, with many kinds of Ticens created now moving in herds. They care about sociality.
Name: Dimension Ticen

Description: A tip of Tucen's tail is made out of minerals.
Name: Dimension Tucen

Description: Many types of Chupacabra have appeared all over the Kingdom, resulting in massive injuries and destruction of property. The Desert Chupacabra is one of the worst.
Name: Dimension Desert Chupacabra

Description: The different thing between the normal Golem is that they follow the regular rules. Even current people could not understand it.
Name: Dimension Sauga

Description: Among the Hogmas, there is someone who obtained the abilities through experiences. But, a sorcerer is not free from the instinct of a Hogma.
Name: Dimension Hogma Shaman

Description: Compared to other animal species, the Vekarabe didn't change much from their original form when they turned into monsters. However, their aggresion definitely is a new addition.
Name: Dimension Vekarabe

Description: The reason that a Dandel's down is more dangerous than keratin is because of it's increased energy and aggression. Thankfully, Dandel of this color are weak during their molting period.
Name: Dimension Orange Dandel

Description: It has no relation with the Kepa. They are demonic beasts even if they do have a rather high intelligence.
Name: Dimension Kepari Shaman

Description: Some say that a Popolion can even shatter glass with its high pitched roar. Popolions of this color are known to be suffering from a type of leukemia. However, it isn't as deadly to them as it is to humans.
Name: Dimension Orange Popolion

Description: Spion usually follow their masters well if trained properly. Of course, most of their masters are demons. Spion Mages are usually born because they have received more power from their masters.
Name: Dimension Spion Mage

Description: While the bottom class of the demon world, their thirst to live better lives is almost frightening.
Name: Dimension Templeslave Mage

Description: Tama is a monster originating from the spores of some plants. It is unclear whether it will still grow from its current form.
Name: Dimension Tama

Description: It is a beast type monster as can be seen in it's appearance and name. Of course, it originates in the demonic world, not ours.
Name: Dimension Lizardman

Description: We don't know which monster's mini version Infroburks are. One thing for sure is that they are vicious.
Name: Dimension Infroburk

Description: While it has maintained its original form, Operor has developed severely aggressive and violent behavior.
Name: Dimension Operor

Description: Please do not look directly into their hoods.
Name: Dimension Hallowventer

Description: It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.
Name: Dimension Ellomago

Description: It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the demon realm and has gone through a lot of change.
Name: Dimension Old Hook

Description: Shredded is a demon monster that was derived from the by-product that results when you transform a monster into a powerful ghost.
Name: Dimension Shredded

Description: A popular theory is that you have to be a demon to use this messenger.
Name: Dimension Desmodus

Description: It is speculated whether this underground spirit has been deformed and corrupted.
Name: Dimension Yognome

Description: The Corylus is a mutant hybrid between plants, animals and minerals.
Name: Dimension Corylus

Description: The sister of Pawnd. Carries a scythe that is much taller than itself. It's name depends on where and what it is born of.
Name: Dimension Pawndel

Description: A soldier that makes up the army of the demons.
Name: Dimension Pawnd

Description: When the demons found Glizardons, they immediately subjugated them into minions. Glizardons that aren't minions are still dangerous to humans.
Name: Dimension Glizardon

Description: Ghosts affected by demons often change their appearance in a way similar to this. Ghosts of this color have are said to have had complexes when they were living.

Description: According to a legend, Minos spent all its life by just fighting. This is because some Demon Lords used them as their servants to check on other Demon Lords.
Name: Dimension Minos

Description: There are some instances Deadborns was born from the shells the Deadborns molted out or from the parts that were seperated from the bodies due to injuries. The original Deadborns had the tendency to discriminate these newcomers and humans also distinguish them from the original ones.

Description: It is simple and effective for Beeteros to camouflage. Please do not touch the swaying leaf as it can stab you.

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places that humans do not know about. Tala Mages are usually affected more by divine energy.

Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected when taking this specific condition into consideration. Description: Tala only appear where divine energy and demon energy meet. There are many more than expected, when taking this specific condition into consideration. Some believe that there are many places with divine energy that humans do not know about.

Description: The Lyecorn is a monster that transformed from a fossilized plant and is therefore very unique.

Description: Lakhtanon are said to have been born in underground lakes or rivers. However, there are traces of civilization on them. There are people that say that this is because humans used to live underground a long time ago.

Description: Lakhof are minerals from underground rivers that transformed on Medzio Diena. They have managed to come above ground since then.

Description: The Lakhof is a monster derived from a mineral that had been near an underground spring. It came aboveground after Medzio Diena. Those of this color were affected by sulphur when they were underground.
